This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney on December 6, 2011, aboard Air Force One en route to Kansas City, Missouri. Carney discusses President Obama's upcoming speech in Osawatomie, Kansas, where he will emphasize the importance of the middle class and fair play in the economy. Carney also addresses the debate over the payroll tax cut extension and expansion, stating that Republicans blocked a vote that would give middle-class Americans a tax break. He mentions that the President is open to a one-year extension of the payroll tax cut and welcomes support from Republicans. Carney also mentions the President's position on Iran, the European debt crisis, and judicial nominees. Finally, he condemns the bombings in Afghanistan that occurred the previous night.